The paper proposes a method for causal discovery based on functional causal models, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The method involves estimating a cascade nonlinear additive noise model, which is a statistical model that can be used to represent indirect causal influences. This suggests that the paper could be relevant to several sub-fields within computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information theory (cs.IT), social and information networks (cs.SI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
